[[!meta title="Installing onto a USB stick, for Windows"]]

We will be using the Universal USB Installer, for more info or more help visit
[http://www.pendrivelinux.com/](http://www.pendrivelinux.com/).

1. Insert a USB stick with at least 2GB of free space
2. [Download the Universal USB Installer](http://www.pendrivelinux.com/downloads/Universal-USB-Installer/Universal-USB-Installer.exe)
3. Click 'Run' when prompted<br/>
   ![Do you want to run or save this file?](usb-install-for-windows/01-run.jpg)
4. If the security dialog appears, confirm by clicking 'Run'<br/>
   ![The publisher could not be verified. Are you sure you want to run this
   software?](usb-install-for-windows/02-run.jpg)
5. Read the licence agreement and choose 'I Agree' to continue<br/>
   ![License Agreement](usb-install-for-windows/03-license-agreement.png)
6. Select T(A)ILS from the dropdown list<br/>
   ![Step 1: Select a Linux Distribution from the dropdown to put on your
   USB](usb-install-for-windows/04-select-tails.png)
7. Click 'Browse' and open the downloaded ISO file<br/>
   ![Step 2: Select your tails*.iso](usb-install-for-windows/05-browse-iso.png)
8. Choose the USB drive<br/>
   ![Step 3: Select your USB Flash Drive Letter
   Only](usb-install-for-windows/06-choose-drive.png)
9. Click 'Create'<br/>
   ![Create](usb-install-for-windows/07-create.png)

